    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 996.2 Carrera 4S represents a pinnacle of the analog driving experience, presented in concours-level condition. Power is delivered via the M96/03 3.6L flat-six, featuring a documented LN Engineering ceramic IMS retrofit and a recently replaced rear main seal. The G96/31 6-speed manual transaxle provides crisp engagement, complemented by an upgraded short-throw shifter. The Widebody chassis retains its factory structural rigidity, supported by a refreshed suspension featuring Bilstein B6 dampers and renewed control arm bushings. All-wheel-drive kinematics are flawless, ensuring optimal torque distribution through the viscous coupling. With a pristine Arctic Silver Metallic finish and a meticulously preserved interior, this example is mechanically sorted with recent borescope inspection confirming zero cylinder scoring. A turn-key acquisition for the discerning collector.",
